cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the use of machine learning to predict smartphone user behavior based on their calendar events and logged time-series smartphone data. This involves analyzing user behavior in different contexts and personalizing the model accordingly. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with context-aware computing, which falls under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
